BT 0 g /F2 15 Tf 226.8 750 Td (A MESSAGE TO GROWN-UPS) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 738 m 552 738 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 715 Td (Dear Parent, Guardian, or Caregiver,) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 698 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 681 Td (This workbook is designed to help your child process grief in) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 664 Td (age-appropriate ways. Children grieve differently than adults.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 647 Td (They may seem fine one moment and fall apart the next.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 630 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 613 Td (HOW TO USE THIS BOOK:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 596 Td (- Go at your child's pace. Don't rush through it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 579 Td (- Be present. Sit with them and answer questions honestly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 562 Td (- It's okay to say 'I don't know' or 'I'm sad too.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 545 Td (- Some pages may be too hard right now. That's okay. Skip them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 528 Td (- Return to pages as many times as needed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 511 Td (- Read body language. Stop if they seem overwhelmed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 494 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 477 Td (THINGS CHILDREN NEED TO HEAR:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (- 'This is not your fault.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 443 Td (- 'It's okay to cry. It's also okay not to cry.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 426 Td (- 'I'm here. I'm not going anywhere.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 409 Td (- 'There is no wrong way to feel.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 392 Td (- 'We will get through this together.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 375 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 358 Td (If your child shows prolonged distress, please consider) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 341 Td (a grief counselor who specializes in children.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
